genresAdvancedInfo.name: pinoy traditional
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Pinoy traditional music is a genre that celebrates the rich cultural heritage of the Philippines. It features indigenous instruments such as the kulintang, kudyapi, and bamboo flute, and is often performed during festivals and special occasions. This genre highlights the diversity of Filipino music, with each region having its own unique style and repertoire.
